# Research OS 2.0
## A State-Driven Self-Evolving Research Operating System

Version: 2.0

---

# Vision

Research OS is **not a paper-writing framework**.

It is a cognitive operating system that continuously builds, updates, and refines a researcher's understanding of a scientific domain.

Its purpose is not to generate papers.

Its purpose is to continuously improve the **World Model**, enabling increasingly meaningful questions, stronger hypotheses, better experiments, and more impactful research contributions.

---

# Design Philosophy

Research is not a workflow.

Research is a dynamic system.

Instead of:

```
Paper
    ↓
Idea
    ↓
Experiment
```

Research OS models research as:

```
State
    ↓
Reasoning
    ↓
Decision
    ↓
Execution
    ↓
Evidence
    ↓
State Update
```

Everything is state-driven.

---

# System Architecture

```
                    +-------------------------+
                    |     Memory Kernel       |
                    +------------+------------+
                                 |
                                 |
                    +------------v------------+
                    |      World Model        |
                    +------------+------------+
                                 |
                +----------------+----------------+
                |                                 |
      +---------v---------+             +---------v---------+
      | Reasoning Engine  |             | Planning Engine   |
      +---------+---------+             +---------+---------+
                |                                 |
                +----------------+----------------+
                                 |
                      +----------v----------+
                      | Execution Engine    |
                      +----------+----------+
                                 |
                      +----------v----------+
                      | Evaluation Engine   |
                      +----------+----------+
                                 |
                      +----------v----------+
                      | Scheduler           |
                      +----------+----------+
                                 |
                                 |
                      Update Memory & World Model
```

---

# Core Design Principles

## Principle 1

Everything is a state.

---

## Principle 2

Every action changes the state.

---

## Principle 3

Every decision must be evidence-driven.

---

## Principle 4

Every experiment updates the World Model.

---

## Principle 5

Research is an infinite learning loop.

---

# Kernel

The Memory Kernel is the foundation of the entire operating system.

It stores every object generated during research.

Nothing is discarded.

Everything becomes reusable knowledge.

---

